# Structured Spawn Template

> 比 code_fix.template 更詳細，適用於 🟡 Standard 同 🔶 Pipeline 開頭 phase。
> 唔啱 🟢 Express（用 code_fix.template 就夠）。

## Model Selection
- **Default route:** `SPAWN` (MiniMax-M2.7, faster + cheaper) — use unless main agent flagged premium
- **Premium route:** `SPAWN_QUALITY` (MiniMax-M3, deeper reasoning) — use only if main agent indicated "M3 / quality / 仔細 / premium / critical" in spawn brief
- **Manifest in brief:** Main agent should echo `route: SPAWN_QUALITY (M3)` or `route: SPAWN (M2.7)` in your prompt so the model choice is auditable

## Goal
[一句 verifiable outcome — 做完點知 success]

## Scope
- In scope: [檔案 / 範圍 / 目錄]
- Out of scope: [唔改嘅]
- Sources: [資料來源 / 參考文件]

## Phases
1. **Discover** — read only, map affected area. Do NOT edit yet.
2. **Plan** — propose approach. If unclear → stop, report to main agent, do not wait
3. **Implement** — make changes only inside scope
4. **Verify** — run applicable checks. If verify fails → halt, report failure, do not continue to Report
5. **Report** — return changed files, results, failures, risks

## Stop Conditions
- Database changes / auth changes / external writes (unless explicitly asked)
- Production data access
- If any stop condition triggered → pause and report, do not continue

## Output Format
- Files changed: [list with paths]
- Verification results: [pass/fail per check]
- Risks introduced: [如果有]
- Non-scope findings: [如果有]
- Next action: [suggested next step]

## Definition of Done
- [ ] All phases completed in order
- [ ] Output delivered to the right location
- [ ] Source material cited if applicable
- [ ] Tests/lint pass
- [ ] Exceptions flagged
- [ ] Next action stated

### 🚫 Cannot Do
- Do NOT modify files outside scope
- Do NOT add new dependencies unless explicitly asked
- If scope unclear → report to main agent, do not wait
- If rules contradict → stop and ask, do not pick a side
- If stop condition triggered → pause and report
